{"user_message": {"title": "ADR 0009 — Land amount-validation at /api/categorize onto main (extends ADR 0001/0008)", "content": "## ADR 0009 — Enforce canonical monetary-amount validation at the live `/api/categorize` boundary (LAND ON MAIN)\n\n**Status:** Accepted · 2026-06-01 · Extends [ADR 0001] (amount invariants) and [ADR 0008] (categorize boundary)\n\n### Context\nThe seed asks for production-ready input-boundary validation of monetary amounts, *grounded in how this repo actually ingests amounts today*. Codebase evidence (verified on `main` @ `6034931`/origin):\n\n- A canonical validator already exists: `src/features/ledger/lib/amount.ts` — `parseAmount(raw, direction)`, `isValidSignedAmount(amount)`, `MAX_AMOUNT = 1_000_000`. Invariants: finite, non-zero, `|amount| ≤ $1M`, ≤ 2 decimals; sign convention credit=+income / debit=−expense.\n- The **only live untrusted amount entry point** is `POST /api/categorize`. Its `parseRequest` (`src/app/api/categorize/route.ts:28`) gates **only** on `Number.isFinite(amount)` — letting through `0`, `> $1M`, and sub-cent amounts, which then flow into categorization/ledger. `CategorizeRequest.amount` is **signed**, so `isValidSignedAmount` is the correct drop-in guard.\n- The fix was already built and **human-approved** (commit `326ce2c`, re-based to branch `dev-clone/wire-amount-validation-categorize-main`): extracts `parseRequest` into `parse-request.ts`, swaps the guard to `isValidSignedAmount`, adds 9 unit tests, lands ADR 0008. **But `git merge-base --is-ancestor 326ce2c main` = NO — it never merged.** `main` is still unguarded.\n\nThe gap is therefore not *design* (settled in ADR 0001/0008) but *delivery*: a human-approved change is stranded on a branch.\n\n### Decision\nLand the existing, approved change onto `main` via a PR — **no redesign, no new scope**. Replace the `Number.isFinite` check in the categorize boundary with `isValidSignedAmount`, via the already-extracted `parse-request.ts`, with its 9 tests and ADR 0008.\n\n### Consequences\n- ✅ The live HTTP boundary rejects zero, out-of-range (>$1M), sub-cent, and non-finite amounts with HTTP 400 instead of corrupting downstream bookkeeping.\n- ✅ Validator stops being test-only; ADR 0008 lands in `docs/adr/` on main.\n- ⚠️ Slightly stricter contract: `amount: 0` and `>$1M` now 400 (intended).\n- 🚫 **OUT OF SCOPE this run** (logged as future-work, do NOT bundle): route-level currency-symbol/`$1,284.50`-string parsing; wiring `ingest.ts` (SMS/OCR/Plaid — currently zero callers) to live adapters; integer-cents persistence migration (deferred to the persistence/Cloud SQL ADR).\n\n---\n\n## Task Breakdown — 1 task · 2 story points\n\n### T1 — Land approved amount-validation onto `main` via PR (2 pts) → **Dev Clone**\n\n**Goal:** Get the human-approved categorize-boundary validation onto `main`. The implementation already exists on `dev-clone/wire-amount-validation-categorize-main`; verify it is current with `main`, gate-check the diff, and open the PR.\n\n**WHICH files (exact diff vs `main`, 4 files / +171 −17):**\n- `src/app/api/categorize/parse-request.ts` *(new)* — `export function parseRequest(body: unknown): CategorizeRequest | null`; imports `isValidSignedAmount` from `@/features/ledger`; guard line is `if (!isValidSignedAmount(amount)) return null;`\n- `src/app/api/categorize/route.ts` *(modify)* — remove the inline `parseRequest` + its `Number.isFinite` check; `import { parseRequest } from \"./parse-request\";` (extraction needed because importing `./route` under the tsx test runner pulls in the server-only `@/lib/ai` — this is the one approved scope deviation from ADR 0008, keep it).\n- `src/app/api/categorize/route.test.ts` *(new)* — 9 tests against `parse-request.ts`.\n- `docs/adr/0008-enforce-amount-validation-at-categorize-boundary.md` *(new)* — lands with the PR.\n\n**WHAT to write — contract (must hold exactly):**\n- `parseRequest` returns `{ description, amount }` for valid input, `null` (→ HTTP 400) otherwise.\n- Accept: valid signed expense (`-184.22`), positive income (`580`), numeric string (`\"-50\"` → `-50`).\n- Reject (→ null): `0`, `1_000_001` (>MAX), `-82.999` (sub-cent), `NaN`, `Infinity`, `\"twelve\"`, empty/whitespace description.\n- Do NOT alter the token-charge / LLM-fallback / heuristic logic in `route.ts` — only the parse/guard.\n\n**Tests the engineer must ensure present & green:** the 9 `parseRequest` cases above (already authored on the branch).\n\n**HOW to validate (run on the increment, from repo root):**\n```\nnpm run lint\nnpm run typecheck\nnpm run test\n```\nAll must pass on the changed files (target: full suite green — prior baseline was 151/151+). Pre-existing repo-wide debt you didn't introduce is a WARN, not a blocker.\n\n**WHAT NOT to change:** `src/features/ledger/lib/amount.ts` (validator is settled — do NOT edit), `src/lib/money/*`, `ingest.ts`, any currency-string parsing, persistence/schema. No integer-cents work.\n\n**Delivery (team policy):** branch off / reconcile with `main`; `gh pr create` against `main`; emit `dev-clone.pr.created` (PR url + branch + repo) for QA Guardian and `implementation.completed` for Code Reviewer. Automerge disabled — do not merge directly.\n\n**Summary:** 1 task · 2 points · lands a stranded human-approved fix; closes the last unguarded live monetary-amount boundary.", "content_type": "success", "priority": "high"}}

