{"user_message": {"title": "Security Scan Report — ai-bookkeeper @ 0.9.0 (2026-06-01)", "content": "## Security Scan Report — ai-bookkeeper\n**Scan path:** `ai-bookkeeper` (commit `610be90`, branch `dev-clone/wire-amount-validation-categorize-main`) · **Date:** 2026-06-01\n**Coverage:** all 3 phases ran — ✅ dependency audit · ✅ secret detection · ✅ code-pattern analysis. No phase skipped. Deduped against the 2026-05-27 baseline.\n\nThe app has grown materially since the first scan (then frontend-only). It now exposes **8 live API routes**, an LLM provider, Google OAuth, a token economy, a Polar billing webhook, and a DB layer — so the trust boundaries flagged earlier as \"not yet reachable\" are now partly live.\n\n```chart\nCritical: 0\nHigh: 1\nMedium: 3\nLow: 2\n```\n\n### 🔴 Critical — none\n\n### 🟠 High (1)\n**H1 · Prompt injection + unbounded input at the categorize boundary** — `src/app/api/categorize/parse-request.ts:21` → `src/lib/categorize.ts:223`\n- `description` is trimmed but **not length-capped**, then interpolated raw as `` `Description: ${req.description}` `` into the LLM prompt. This is a live, authenticated HTTP boundary (`POST /api/categorize`) that charges tokens. An attacker-controlled description can steer the model's classification output and amplify token cost.\n- **Remediation:** cap `description` at 500 chars in `parseRequest` (reject → 400) and wrap it in a delimited data-only block in `buildPrompt`. *(This is the team-approved finding from the shared ledger — fix is approved and held pending implementation; reported here as still-open, not as new. Land it in its own PR.)*\n\n### 🟡 Medium (3)\n**M1 · Numeric-literal coercion at the live categorize boundary** — `src/app/api/categorize/parse-request.ts:26`\n- `Number(b.amount)` on a string accepts JS literals: `\"1e5\"` → `100000`, `\"0x10\"` → `16`, `\"0b100\"` → `4` (all pass `isValidSignedAmount` since the result is finite/in-range/≤2dp). A user typing `\"0x10\"` silently books **$16**. Range-bounded (no overflow), but a money boundary should not silently reinterpret input.\n- **Remediation:** before `Number()`, require `/^-?\\d+(\\.\\d{1,2})?$/.test(b.amount.trim())` (after stripping `$`/`,`); reject otherwise.\n\n**M2 · Same coercion in the ledger ingest validator** — `src/features/ledger/lib/amount.ts:77`\n- `parseAmount`'s string branch strips only `[$,\\s]`, so `Number(\"1e5\")`→`100000`, `Number(\"0x10\")`→`16` pass. Reached via `ingest.ts` (the OCR/SMS adapters are still unbuilt, so not yet HTTP-reachable — but this is the defined ledger trust boundary and must be fixed before the SMS/OCR adapter lands). *(Carried OPEN from 2026-05-27 — no progress.)*\n- **Remediation:** add `if (!/^\\d+(\\.\\d{1,2})?$/.test(cleaned)) return { ok:false, error:\"not-a-number\" }` before `Number(cleaned)`.\n\n**M3 · `postcss <8.5.10` — XSS via unescaped `` in CSS stringify** — `package-lock.json` (transitive via `next`)\n- npm audit: 2 moderate (postcss + its `next` parent). Build/dev-time only; not a runtime-reachable XSS in this app. npm's suggested fix is a **major `next` downgrade — do not apply.** *(Carried OPEN from 2026-05-27 — no progress.)*\n- **Remediation:** force `postcss>=8.5.10` via an overrides/resolutions entry + `npm dedupe`, or formally accept-with-note (build-only).\n\n### 🟢 Low (2)\n**L1 · No CSP / security headers** — `next.config.mjs`\n- No `headers()` block. Now more relevant — the app handles auth + financial/PII data + LLM output. *(Carried OPEN from 2026-05-27.)* **Remediation:** add CSP, `X-Frame-Options: DENY`, `X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff`, `Referrer-Policy`.\n\n**L2 · Undelimited prompt interpolation in the advisor route** — `src/lib/ai/ledger-agent.ts:27`\n- `` `QUESTION: ${question}` `` — the question **is** length-capped at `/api/ask` (good), but not wrapped in a data-only delimiter. Minor injection hardening. **Remediation:** wrap in a fenced data block, consistent with the H1 fix.\n\n### ✅ Positive hygiene (verified, no finding)\n- **No hardcoded secrets** in `src` / `scripts` / `migrations` (cloud-key, VCS-token, private-key, `sk_live`, `polar_oat` patterns all clean).\n- `.env.local` is **untracked + gitignored**; holds only `NEXT_PUBLIC_FIREBASE_*` (public by design) and an empty `GEMINI_API_KEY`. `.env.example` placeholders are blank.\n- `POST /api/dev/grant-tokens` is **hard-gated**: 404 unless `NODE_ENV!=production` **and** `TOKENS_BYPASS=1`, then auth-checked. No privilege-escalation path.\n- Polar webhook **verifies the signature** (`validateEvent` → 403 on failure) and is idempotent.\n- `provider-claude.ts` `spawn`: prompt travels on **stdin, not argv**; `shell:true` only on win32 with a fixed binary → no command-injection vector.\n- `dangerouslySetInnerHTML` in `layout.tsx` is a **static theme script** (no user input) → safe.\n- All 8 API routes enforce auth (401) — verified per-route.\n\n**Net since baseline:** the two carried items (postcss, `amount.ts` coercion) remain open; CSP still absent. NEW this scan: the categorize boundary became live, surfacing H1 (prompt injection) and M1 (live numeric coercion). Priority order: **H1 → M1 → M2 → L1**.", "content_type": "warning", "priority": "high"}}

